<!--Basic-->
Document Type Declaration: It's best to state the document type
ex: <!DOCTYPE html-->
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Necessity: These 3 tags are necessary for a html code
1. HTML Tags: Every code is under this
ex: <html></html>
2. Head Tags: This is a setup for website (name, languages...)
ex: <head></head>
3. Body Tags: Every visible part is code under this
ex: <body></body>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Comments: Information to coder ignored by computer
ex: <!--Comments-->
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HTML Attributes: Provide additional information about elements
Always specified in the start tag, usually come in name/value pairs
ex: <img src="Path">                    -->   src attribute specifies the path to the pic or URL
ex: <a href="URL">                      -->   href attribute specifies the URL of the page the link goes to
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Path: The path has 2 ways to specifies
1. Absolute URL: Link to different website
ex: src="https://.../.../.../image.jpg"
2. Relative URL: Link within the website
ex: src="/images/img.jpg"
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tags:
There is 2 types of tags, container tag and empty tag.
1. container tag: has 2 tags and content inside them, the second tag is same as the first but add one more '/'
ex: <p>mmm</p> <h1>Heading</h1>
2. empty tag: only one tag
ex: <img>
